---
// Honest founder note. Removes the fabricated Long Beach / $3.2M anecdote and the
// "ex-CargoWise consultant" line (unverified). Keeps the intent: humanize right before
// the final CTA. The story is the industry reality, not a made-up customer.
---
<section class="bg-white py-20 md:py-24 border-t border-black/5">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 reveal">
    <p class="eyebrow">A note from the team</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 text-h2 font-bold text-navy-900">Why we built this.</h2>

    <div class="mt-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-navy-900/85 space-y-5">
      <p>
        Talk to ten mid-market freight forwarders and you will hear ten variations on the same problem.
        Enterprise TMS vendors quote six-month implementations and five-figure monthly bills. The cloud-native
        &ldquo;disruptors&rdquo; assume you already have a full-stack engineer. Spreadsheets are everywhere.
      </p>
      <p>
        In the middle of all that is an operator trying to respond to an RFQ before the shipper takes lunch
        with a competitor. Nobody was building software for that operator on a realistic budget, so we did.
      </p>
      <p>
        LogisticsPrizm is pre-launch and we are picky about who we onboard first. We would rather have twenty
        Founding Customers we can actually help than two hundred we can&#39;t. If the pitch above resonates,
        the demo is twenty minutes and we load your own lanes into a sandbox beforehand. You decide the rest.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 flex items-center gap-4">
      <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-prizm-500 to-prizm-700"></div>
      <div>
        <div class="font-semibold text-navy-900">The founding team</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-navy-900/60">LogisticsPrizm</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
